  "texts": [
    "Recently, Tsai et al. (2023b) propose high-dimensional representers, a novel extension of Yeh et al.'s (2018) representer theorem to additional types of regularization.",
    "Specifically, Tsai et al.",
    "consider decomposable regularization functions (Negahban et al., 2012).",
    "Formally, a regularization function r",
    "Examples of decomposable regularizers include L 1 -norm (Tibshirani, 1996) and the matrix nuclear norm (Yuan et al., 2007; Recht, 2011; Yang et al., 2017)."
  ]
}